Mexico’s Coffee Exports Decline 16% Last Month, Amecafe Says

-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-04-06T20:17:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/mexico-s-coffee-exports-decline-16-last-month-amecafe-says.html
Mexico ’s coffee exports declined 16
percent last month from a year earlier to 331,318 bags,
according to a e-mailed statement today from the country’s
coffee association, Amecafe.  Mexico’s output in the season that began on Oct. 1 is
estimated at 4 million bags, Rodolfo Trampe Taubert, the
executive coordinator of the organization, said on March 31.  A bag of coffee weighs 60 kilograms (132 pounds).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
 ialmeida3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
